      "role": "user",
      "content": "No additional sensors need to remain active. The protocol is clear: once the data burst is verified, the power cutoff hits the main logic board. This isn't about data integrity; it's a hard shutdown to preserve what's left of the battery.\n\nThe mission parameters will remain on hold until the next window. Proceed with the cataloging as instructed.",
